By Balaji Subramanian, Founder and CEO, Promethium, Inc.

Public transportation systems frequently go through evolution from rail-based systems to modern bus network. A common theme across the different systems is a dialectic between the bus network and having metro lines/monorails that act as last-mile connectors or as trip saviours. This has been the theme played out on several occasions with varying degrees of success across the world today.

Smithtown, NY: From Buses to Light-Rail Monorail

The Smithtown Santa Express is an example of evolving from an old model to a new «going-green» model, creating a popular experience for tourists and local residents. This model replaces the Santa’s Exhibit on the Washington [Orient] Railway line with MLFBs. MLFBs are the next generation buses designed fto provide the flexibility of a full-fledged smart bus with the comfort level of a light rail train. A sustainable and energy-efficient model of transportation.
